title.narrative: Libya Elections and Legislative Strengthening Activity

description.narrative: (Libya): .The Libya Elections and Legislative Strengthening Activity (LELSA) will support Libya to implement presidential and parliamentary national elections, as well as provide continued support for municipal elections, and support Libyan-led initiatives to advance reconciliation at the national and local levels to boost civic and voter participation. Assistance will include technical assistance to Libya's election bodies to implement credible, transparent, inclusive, and secure elections; support for voter registration and outreach, including through information campaigns, dialogues, and candidate debates; assistance to strengthen and secure voting systems; electoral security; impartial media; and work with relevant government entities and civil society on elections laws and the constitutional basis for future elections and community level violence prevention and peacebuilding. These activities advance U.S. policy to support Libya's political transition, stabilization, and security with the goal of building a unified, inclusive, and accountable government. Legislative activities include capacity building to legislative bodies and their staff on legislative drafting, consensus building, leadership, and other skills to improve the quality and effectiveness of legislation, particularly as it relates to any proposed elections. Assistance also aims to increase the legislature's capacity to be responsive to the people it serves; enhance public participation in policy-making; and empower civil society, including women, persons with disabilities, and indigenous groups to be an avenue for advocacy. LELSA will also support national reconciliation and provide capacity building to civil society and journalists to counter corrosive influences, including hate speech and disinformation..This IM accounts for $300K of the Women's Leadership earmark. ..

description.narrative: (Libya): Libya's economy relies on oil revenue, and the lack of transparency and perception of inequitable distribution of oil revenue are key drivers of conflict. Libya's Public Financial Management (LPFM) activity assists the Government of Libya in strengthening the macroeconomic and fiscal foundations for sustainable and inclusive growth and enhances transparency, accountability, and oversight in the use of public resources within core Libyan governance systems.During its fourth year of implementation (2022-23), LPFM will provide technical assistance to four key Libyan institutions: the Central Bank, the General Electric Company, the Renewable Energy Authority, and the Audit Bureau. These institutions are key to the transparent management of Libya's resource wealth and are important pillars of economic stability. Energy demand is at a critical point in Libya and even with the large oil and gas reserves, demand outstrips supply. LPFM will help enhance the national capacity to improve energy efficiency, reduce demand, and introduce renewable energy. USAID's assistance will help reduce energy consumption by 20% within five years. LPFM will strengthen the CBL's internal policies, procedures, and control systems to allow for transparent public financial management that is in greater conformity with international standards. LPFM's technical assistance will help the Libyan Audit Bureau (LAB) exercise its role as Libya's main accountability actor and allow it to conduct credible and transparent audits of Libya's executive branch. USAID's assistance will help generate better employment opportunities for women in government institutions that are historically dominated by men and help empower more women to assume technical and leadership roles. This IM accounts for $2,150,000 of the Clean Energy-Indirect earmark and $200K of the Women's Leadership earmark.
